#Text=Sweden
#Text=Sweden ( Swedish : Sverige ) is the largest of the Nordic countries by size and population , with about 10 million inhabitants .
#Text=It borders Norway and Finland and is connected to Denmark via a bridge-tunnel across Öresund .

#Text=Visitors can experience deep forests and many lakes , the heritage from the Viking Age and the 17th-century Swedish Empire , the glamour of the Nobel Prize , and the country 's successful pop music scene .
#Text=Regions
#Text=The three traditional lands of Sweden , Götaland , Svealand and Norrland , are further divided into 25 provinces ( landskap ) , which largely define Swedish people 's cultural identity .
#Text=The provinces mostly coincide with the 21 counties ( län ) , the mid-level political entities .
#Text=The 290 municipalities ( kommun ) , are the bottom-level political entities , typically consisting of a town or a city , and the surrounding countryside , including small villages .
#Text=Some municipalities used to hold city ( stad ) privileges , and still style themselves as such , though there is no legal distinction .
#Text=Most municipalities have their own visitor centre .

#Text=Though Swedish people rarely have strong feelings for their country , most of them are patriotic for their province or hometown , and appreciate anything good that a traveller can say about them .
#Text=Cities

#Text=Understand
#Text=The " Nordic model " of economics and social policy was largely developed by Swedish social democrats and liberals during the early 20th century .
#Text=The foundation is a strong welfare state , combined with market economics .
#Text=Swedish society , as it has become through this policy , is often described as " folkhemmet " , comparing solidarity in the society with that in a family :
#Text=History
#Text=In ancient times , Sweden was inhabited by the Suiones ( svear ) in Svealand and the Geats ( götar ) in Götaland .
#Text=Some of these participated in Viking expeditions ( see Vikings and the Old Norse ) , and are said to have founded the first kingdoms in Russia .
#Text=Written sources from the Viking Age are few and short .

#Text=Around AD 1000 , Christianity replaced Norse paganism , Suiones and Geats united under one king ( probably Olof Skötkonung ) , and the first cities were founded ; among them Sigtuna , Uppsala and Skara .
#Text=With Christianity came written chronicles and stone architecture , which have provided the afterworld with better historical detail than earlier remnants .
#Text=Swedish kings christianized and annexed Finland .
#Text=During the 14th and 15th century , Sweden was a subject of the Kalmar Union with Norway and Denmark .
#Text=Gustav Vasa liberated Sweden from Danish rule , was elected as king in 1523 , and is regarded as the founder of modern Sweden .
#Text=He also reformed the church to Lutheran-Protestant .
#Text=Today 's Sweden is a secular state with very few church-goers .

#Text=During the 17th century Sweden rose as a Great Power , through several successful wars ( such as the Thirty Years ' War ) , where kings such as Gustavus Adolphus and Charles X annexed Scania , Halland and Bohuslän from Denmark , as well as temporary possessions in the Baltic countries and northern Germany .
#Text=In the early 18th century , an alliance of Denmark , Poland and the Russian Empire defeated Swedish king Charles XII , marking the end of the Swedish Empire .
#Text=In 1809 , Sweden was again defeated by Russia , which annexed Finland .
#Text=The country has been at peace since 1814 ; the country has a high peace profile , with internationally renowned names such as Raoul Wallenberg , Dag Hammarskjöld , Olof Palme and Hans Blix .
#Text=Sweden is a monarchy by constitution , but King Carl XVI Gustaf has no executive power .
#Text=Sweden is a developed post-industrial society with an advanced welfare state .
#Text=The standard of living and life expectancy rank among the highest in the world .
#Text=Sweden joined the European Union in 1995 , but decided by a referendum in 2003 not to commit to the European Monetary Union and the euro currency .

#Text=Leadership of Sweden has for the larger part of the 20th century been dominated by the Social Democratic Party , which started out at the end of the 19th century as a labor movement ( coalitions of centre-right liberal/conservative parties held the power 1976 – 1982 and 2006 – 2014 ) .
#Text=Sweden has a strong tradition of being an open , yet discreet country .
#Text=Citizens sometimes appear to be quite reserved at first , but once they get to know who they are dealing with , they 'll be as warm and friendly as you 'd wish .

#Text=Privacy is regarded as a key item and many visitors , for example mega-stars in various lines of trade , have many times realized that they mostly can walk the streets of the cities virtually undisturbed .
#Text=Sweden houses the Nobel Prize committee for all the prizes except the peace prize , which is hosted in Oslo , a memento of the Swedish-Norwegian union that was dissolved in 1905 .
